RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR WASHINGTON-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $12,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUTES SEA GYPSY brushed with KIKI'S CRUSADER at the start, then was unhurried early, moved forward between horses on the turn, came four-wide into the stretch and finished fast to be up in the final sixteenth to win going away. SHILSHOLE BAY brushed at the start with FLY PARKER FLY then dueled with SOLO UN BESO from along the outside, opened clear entering the stretch but was unable to resist the winner late while clearly second best. JEWELED AGAIN saved ground while being allowed to settle, angled out leaving the three-sixteenths pole for room and was gaining late. FLY PARKER FLY was brushed at the start then saved ground chasing the leaders, came three-wide into the stretch but lacked a rally. KIKI'S CRUSADER was brushed at the start then was forwardly placed early while racing two-wide and weakened. SOLO UN BESO dueled for the lead from along the outside to the stretch and tired. SODA SPRINGS dropped back early and failed to seriously threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: Jeweled Again
ENTRY.OWNER: Warlock Stables Roche Michael and Barrett Roddina A
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, saved ground, angled out 3/16, late gain

ENTRY.NAME: Fly Parker Fly
ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed start, chased, three-wide entering, lacked rally

ENTRY.NAME: Shilshole Bay
ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed start, dueled inside, clear entering, caught, 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Lutes Sea Gypsy
ENTRY.OWNER: Horse Haven Creek Farm and Barking Dogs
ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed start, unhurried, 4-wide entering, up final 1/16

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 8500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE NOVEMBER 11, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RED NOVA vied with PRESKITT from along the inside, opened a clear lead nearing the stretch, drifted out entering the stretch and maintained a safe advantage. PRESKITT vied with RED NOVA, dropped back slightly nearing the stretch, drifted out nearing the three-sixteenths pole, could not reach the winner but held on well for second. MISCHIEF MAMA saved ground while being allowed to settle in stride, slipped through during the drive and finished in a mild rally. MOSCOW LADY saved ground while being prominent early, came two-wide into the stretch and lacked a rally. TYCHE AWAITS YOU saved ground while being unhurried and showed some interest late. GOLD ROSE was forwardly placed early, came four-wide into the stretch, gave way during the drive and was vanned off following the finish.

ENTRY.NAME: Red Nova
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, drifted out 3/16, maintained advantage

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Estate of William Currin, Judy Miller,Oakbrook Farm & Valk

ENTRY.NAME: Gold Rose
ENTRY.COMMENT: forwardly placed, 4-w entering, gave way, vanned off

ENTRY.NAME: Tyche Awaits You
ENTRY.OWNER: Crowe Shelly M and Richards Jay

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 57. Maiden Claiming Purse 16500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 119 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BETTY LUTE prompted the early pace set by WINANYWAYUCAN from along the outside, took the lead nearing the five-sixteenths pole, opened a clear lead entering the stretch and maintained a safe advantage. SPEIGHTFUL CAT was two-wide while being reserved off the early pace, came four-wide into the stretch and finished fast. ALWAYS GALLANT saved ground while being unhurried, angled out to be five-wide entering the stretch and finished in a mild rally. ROCKIT A DAY saved ground while being allowed to settle, slipped through during the drive but lacked a rally. WINANYWAYUCAN set the pressured pace to the five-sixteenths pole and tired/. FLYING COURAGE broke in the air to get away behind the field, then dropped further back and failed to seriously threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: Winanywayucan
ENTRY.OWNER: Rancho Viejo Baze Lisa A and Martinez Juan L

ENTRY.NAME: Flying Courage
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in air, dropped back, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Betty Lute
ENTRY.OWNER: Kvinsland John and Horse Haven Creek Farm
ENTRY.COMMENT: prompted 2-wide, led 5/16, opened clear, held safe advantage

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 9000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUMMANUS vied for the lead from along the inside, opened clear nearing the eighth pole and then was all out to prevail narrowly. PERFECT ONE was bumped at the stat by TAP THE BANK, then was reserved off the pace, rallied five-wide into the stretch, came in during the drive brushing with NATION OF FAITH and finished fast. NATION OF FAITH was allowed to settle in stride, rallied four-wide into the stretch, was brushed by PERFECT ONE during the stretch and steadied nearing the wire from between horses and finished willingly. AGRIGENTO prompted the pace from along the inside to the stretch and weakened late. WEGOTBEERONICE was forwardly placed while racing three-wide, steadied nearing the three-sixteenths pole in tight while tiring. SENOR FABULOSO dropped back early, came five-wide into the stretch and improved his position. TIME 'N TIME AGAIN saved ground while racing in the middle of the field, steadied nearing the quarter pole when the rider less horse moved up beside him, angled out for the drive and failed to menace. TEACHERSBUGSAROO saved ground chasing the pace from along the inside and tired. TAP THE BANK bobbled slightly at the start, then went in to bump PERFECT ONE and unseated his rider. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE STRETCH RUN AND FOUND THAT WHILE PERFECT ONE CREATED CONTACT THAT HE DID NOT COST NATION OF FAITH A POSITION SO MADE NO CHANGE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

ENTRY.NAME: Summanus
ENTRY.OWNER: Bussey Kenneth Indigenous Stable and Filos Stables
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, clear 1/8, just lasted, all out

ENTRY.NAME: Nation of Faith
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, 4-wide entering, brushed drive, steadied late, willingly

ENTRY.NAME: Perfect One
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, reserved, 5-wide entering, came in drive, rallied

ENTRY.NAME: Tap the Bank
ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled, came in, bumped, lost rider

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 5 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 89. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Maiden Races, Claiming Races And Starters Races For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).

CLAIM.OWNER: Carmody Jerry Sneesby John and Baze Lisa

RACE.FOOTNOTES: OLYMPIC LEGEND vied with AMERICAN GRIT for the early lead, disposed of that one after a quarter mile and gradually increased his advantage. THE CALABRESE KID was unhurried early, rallied five-wide into the stretch and closed strongly. MIRROR IMAGE was reserved off the early pace, came four-wide into the stretch and finished in a mild rally. CROOKED FINGER RAY was allowed to settle early, came two-wide into the stretch to offer a mild bid and then flattened out during the drive. WESTERN RULE was forwardly place while racing three-wide but lacked a rally. AMERICAN GRIT vied for the lead from along the outside for a quarter mile and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Olympic Legend
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, clear after 1/4, increased advantage

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Lawrence Marshall Opas MD,Frank Sinatra MD & John Jain MD

ENTRY.NAME: Western Rule
ENTRY.OWNER: Belvoir Howard E and Buchanan Robert D

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 96. Claiming Purse 18000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $12,500, allowed 3 lbs. (Maiden Races, Claiming Races And Starters Races For $12,500 O r Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FANTASTIC DAY dropped well back early, rallied three-wide into the stretch, angled to the inside leaving the three-sixteenths and finished fast to be up in the final strides. PESO was reserved off the early pace, came two-wide entering the stretch, caught the leaders at the three-sixteenths pole, disputed the issue from that point and just missed in a game effort. ALLEVA broke slowly to get away behind the field, moved up four-wide on the turn, caught the leaders entering the stretch, disputed the issue from that point but wasn't able to stay with the top two late in a good try. A VIEW FROM ABOVE chased the pace from along the inside, came three-wide into the stretch and weakened. NEW EVERY MORNING was forwardly placed to the stretch while racing two-wide and tired. POLACCO set the pace for three furlongs, gave way when headed and was eased in the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Peso
ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved, 2-wide entering, caught leaders 3/16, game effort

ENTRY.NAME: Alleva
ENTRY.COMMENT: off slow, 4-wide turn, caught leaders entering, good try

ENTRY.NAME: Fantastic Day
ENTRY.COMMENT: dropped back, 3-w entering, angled inside, up final strides

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Claiming Purse 8500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SINGLE MERIT sprinted clear shortly the start, saved ground setting the pace and was unchallenged. CRAWLINGBACKTOYOU saved ground while being allowed to settle, just avoided the fallen horse and rider then held on fairly well for second. EXIT STAGE LEFT was reserved off the early pace, moved up three-wide on the turn, angled out at the five-sixteenths pole to avoid the fallen horse aand rider while steadying, came six-wide into the stretch and finished in a mild rally. POCO DIABLO ROJO ducked in sharply at the start crossing behind CRAWLINGBACKTOYOU, the was unhurried, steadied nearing the five-sixteenths pole to avoid the fallen horses and rider and finished willingly when clear. T. J. HOUSE bobbled at the start then was allowed to settled, steadied and went out nearing the five-sixteenths pole avoiding the fallen horse and rider and was unable to menace while being in hand during the drive. HASTA LUEGO was unhurried early, steadied nearing the five-sixteenths pole avoiding the fallen horse and rider and failed to threaten while being in hand during the drive. HE'S A FLYIN chased the winner while racing two-wide, appeared to go wrong nearing the five-sixteenths pole and fell and was vanned off. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY WITH REGARDS TO HE'S A FLYIN BUT AFTER VIEWING THE FILMS MADE NO CHANGE IN THE ORDER OF FINISH.

ENTRY.NAME: Poco Diablo Rojo
ENTRY.COMMENT: ducked in sharply start, unhurried, steadied 5/16, willingly

ENTRY.NAME: Exit Stage Left
ENTRY.OWNER: Hagen Ronald A Hagen Nina and Bullock Steve

ENTRY.NAME: T. J. House
ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled start, steadied 5/16, angled out, no menace
